						"title": "Machine learning and artificial intelligence security ",
						"subtitle": "Tools, technologies, and detection surfaces",
						"copy": "As organizations increasingly integrate machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) LLMs into their operations, they face a growing array of security and data privacy challenges. The Forrester report, \"Machine learning and artificial intelligence security: Tools, technologies, and detection surfaces,\" addresses these concerns by examining the evolving threat landscape, LLMs and AI sprawl, and the tools available to secure AI and ML systems.\n\nThis report serves as a critical resource for security and risk leaders aiming to understand and mitigate the unique challenges posed by AI and ML technologies.\n\nKey insights from the report include:\n\n- __GenAI opportunities and threats__\n- __Emergence of AI/ML security architectures__\n- __Zero Trust AI frameworks__\n- __Expansion of automated detection techniques__\n- __Necessity for security operations automation__\n- __Threat Intelligence powered by proactive AI algorithms__\n- __The AI threat to GRC__ \n",
